abstract: A look around the nation at the best in college football from Week 9.
snippet: A look around the nation at the best in college football from Week 9.
lead_paragraph: KEVIN DECKER The New Hampshire quarterback had 335 yards of total offense and scored the go-ahead touchdown to lead host New Hampshire over Rhode Island, 31-24. Decker led an efficient six-play, 68-yard drive in the third quarter, erasing a 3-point deficit with a 1-yard touchdown run. He finished 14 of 21 for 257 yards.

headline.main: The Day's Best in College Football
